HEADWORD: Eruginous
<hw>E*ru"gi*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧rugineux</ets>. See <er>⟦ae⟧ruginous</er>.]</ety>
<def>Partaking of the substance or nature of copper, or of the rust of
copper; resembling the rust of copper or verdigris;
⟦ae⟧ruginous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

